5|$|The menu uses {{locally grown}} produce from Powys and Shropshire, {{and is a}} {{combination}} of classic and modern French cuisine with seasonal changes. Dishes include a <b>pork</b> <b>belly</b> main from the nearby Neuadd Fach baconry, which is served with an apple mousseline, pear and au jus. A monkfish main course comes served with a langoustine consommé and a Brussels sprout purée. Other French courses include a French onion soup and a cheese soufflé. Desserts served include a nougat tube filled with white chocolate and passion fruit mousse, and a trio of lemon pots.|$|E
25|$|On 1 February 2017, The Ohio Pork Council {{released}} a report that demand for <b>pork</b> <b>belly</b> (bacon) product is outpacing supply. As of December 2016 national frozen <b>pork</b> <b>belly</b> inventory totaled , the lowest level in 50 years.|$|E
