50|$|If any market, such as <b>pork</b> <b>bellies,</b> had no speculators, only {{producers}} (hog farmers) {{and consumers}} (butchers, etc.) would participate. With fewer {{players in the}} market, {{there would be a}} larger spread between the current bid and ask price of <b>pork</b> <b>bellies.</b> Any new entrant in the market who wanted to trade <b>pork</b> <b>bellies</b> would be forced to accept this illiquid market and might trade at market prices with large bid-ask spreads or even face difficulty finding a co-party to buy or sell to.|$|R
